Package: waterml
Title: Fetch and analyze data from CUAHSI WaterML web service
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: "Jiří Kadlec <jirikadlec2@gmail.com> [aut, cre]"
Description: The waterml package lets you connect to any CUAHSI WaterOneFlow web service from 
any hydroserver. To see list of available hydroservers, see http://hiscentral.cuahsi.org .
The supported version of WaterML is 1.1.
The package has three functions:
    GetVariables(): Show a data.frame with all variables on the server
	GetSites():     Show a data.frame with all sites on the server
	GetValues():    Given a site code, variable code, start time and end time, fetch a
	                data.frame of all the data values. The data.frame has two columns: time and DataValue.
					This function has an optional "daily" parameter
					you can set daily="max", daily="min" or daily="mean" to get aggregated daily values.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2)
License: BSD
LazyData: true
